          <source>Processing Notification Messages in List Controls</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>As users click column headers, drag icons, edit labels, and so on, the list control (<bpt id="p1">[</bpt>CListCtrl<ept id="p1">](../mfc/reference/clistctrl-class.md)</ept>) sends notification messages to its parent window.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Handle these messages if you want to do something in response.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, when the user clicks a column header, you might want to sort the items based on the contents of the clicked column, as in Microsoft Outlook.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Process <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>WM_NOTIFY<ept id="p1">**</ept> messages from the list control in your view or dialog class.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the Properties window to create an <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>OnChildNotify<ept id="p1">](../mfc/reference/cwnd-class.md#cwnd__onchildnotify)</ept> handler function with a switch statement based on which notification message is being handled.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For a list of the notifications a list control can send to its parent window, see <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>List View Control Reference<ept id="p1">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/bb774737)</ept> in the <ph id="ph1">[!INCLUDE[winSDK](../atl/includes/winsdk_md.md)]</ph>.</source>
